==English==

===Noun===
'''firecall'''

# Any method established to provide emergency access to a secure information system.  In the event of a critical error or abnormal end, unprivileged users can gain access to key systems to correct the problem.  When a firecall is used, there is usually a bureaucratic review process to ensure that the access was used properly to correct a problem.  These methods generaly either provide a one-time use User ID or one-time password.

===Quotations===
* '''2001''' December, Thomas R Peltier, ''Information Security Policies, Procedures, and Standards'', page 283, CRC Press
*: Special procedures and audited “'''firecall'''” userids <!--sic--> have been established for application, system, and network troubleshooting activities.
* '''2003''' September, Terri Hill et al., ''HP NonStop Server Security'', page 92, Digital Press
*: All Privileged IDs should be treated as ‘check out’ or ‘'''firecall'''’ IDs.